OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,409,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F408A1783952425
OL,3,CPlymouth experts warn of impact of
OL,4,Cmarine heatwave on sea life
OL,6,FPlymouth's waters registered at 19.4C
OL,7,F- 3.7C above temperatures expected at
OL,8,Fthis time of year, which he describes
OL,9,Fas "astonishing".
OL,11,F"It means marine life is having to put
OL,12,Fup with conditions that are totally
OL,13,Fdifferent and much warmer. We just
OL,14,Fdon't know what the thresholds are for
OL,15,Fsome of those species," he says.
OL,17,FMr Frost says this shows climate
OL,18,Fchange predictions "that we would get
OL,19,Fmore heatwaves, they would last longer
OL,20,Fand more intense" are proving accurate.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/6
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,409,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F408A1783952425
OL,3,CPlymouth experts warn of impact of
OL,4,Cmarine heatwave on sea life
OL,6,F"Off the back of three years of marine
OL,7,Fheatwaves, we can say those
OL,8,Fpredictions are coming true, and we're
OL,9,Fseeing the result of climate change
OL,10,Fglobally, which is not normal".
OL,12,FHe says that there is concern that
OL,13,Fonce El Nino does kick in - a
OL,14,Fnaturally occurring climate pattern
OL,15,Fthat can influence weather across the
OL,16,Fglobe - any indirect effects of that
OL,17,Fon top of global warming and marine
OL,18,Fheatwaves are going to start
OL,19,F"stressing the system".
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/6
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
