OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,409,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F408A1783952425
OL,3,CPlymouth experts warn of impact of
OL,4,Cmarine heatwave on sea life
OL,6,FThe Met Office said surface waters in
OL,7,Fnorth-west European seas are currently
OL,8,Fexperiencing moderate to severe marine
OL,9,Fheatwave conditions, with many areas
OL,10,Fcurrently categorised as "strong" and
OL,11,Fsome "severe".
OL,13,FThis means waters have reached
OL,14,Ftemperatures usually expected in
OL,15,FAugust and are on average 2C warmer
OL,16,Fthan usual.
OL,18,FThey have even reached more than 4-5C
OL,19,Fwarmer locally in some offshore parts
OL,20,Fof the English and Welsh coasts, the
OL,21,Fforecasting agency said.
OL,26,@rD@ZOUrD@aO]sD@FOUsD@MO]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/6
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
